<item>
            <title>[LU-17497] Prevent setting incorrect values for identity and rsi upcall</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17497</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Identity upcall can be set via &lt;tt&gt;lctl set_param mdt.*.identity_upcall=xxx&lt;/tt&gt;, and rsi upcall can be set via &lt;tt&gt;lctl set_param sptlrpc.gss.rsi_upcall=xxx&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Possible values are a valid path to an executable, and also &lt;tt&gt;NONE&lt;/tt&gt; to disable identity upcall. In order to prevent Lustre issues due to the upcall incorrectly set, we should check for input value, and return an error if it is not correct (along with a kind message giving accepted values).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
